-------------------------------

2.1. Grants
    Each Contributor hereby grants You a world-wide, royalty-free,
    non-exclusive license:

    (a) under intellectual property rights (other than patent or trademark)
        Licensable by such Contributor to use, reproduce, make available,
        modify, display, perform, distribute, and otherwise exploit
        its Contributions, either on an unmodified basis, with Modifications,
        or as part of a Larger Work; and

    (b) under Patent Claims of such Contributor to make, use, sell, offer
        for sale, have made, import, and otherwise transfer either its
        Contributions or its portion of the Larger Work.

2.2. Effective Date
    The licenses granted in Section 2.1 with respect to any Contribution
    become effective for each Contribution on the date the Contributor
    first distributes such Contribution.

2.3. Limitations on Grant Scope
    The licenses granted in this Section 2 shall not apply to any
    software or other material that You distribute in violation of this
    License.

2.4. Termination
    If You fail to comply with any term(s) of this License, then Your
    rights under this License terminate automatically.

2.5. Recipient Rights
    If You distribute Covered Software, You must inform recipients of
    their rights under this License.

3. Responsibilities
-------------------

3.1. Distribution of Source Code Form
    When You distribute Covered Software in Source Code Form You must:

    (a) provide a copy of this License, including the rights and
        responsibilities herein, with each copy of the Covered Software;

    (b) make available the Source Code Form of the Covered Software,
        including any modifications, in a manner that is either:

        (i) distributed with the Covered Software; or

        (ii) made available by means of a network server at no charge,
            provided You inform recipients in writing of the network
            location; or

        (iii) provided for no charge on a physical medium customarily
              used for software interchange;

    (c) inform recipients how to obtain a copy of the Source Code Form;

    (d) ensure that the Source Code Form you make available is the
        version corresponding to the Covered Software you distribute;

    (e) ensure that the Source Code Form you make available is either
        the version used to create the Covered Software or a version
        reasonably suitable for taking modifications; and

    (f) accompany the Covered Software with a notice file that lists the
        names of all Contributors, as well as the date of any recent
        modifications.

3.2. Distribution of Executable Form
    When You distribute Covered Software in Executable Form You must:

    (a) comply with Section 3.1; and

    (b) provide a copy of the notice file with each copy of the Covered
        Software;

    (c) inform recipients of any known license terms for the Covered
        Software;

    (d) inform recipients where to obtain a copy of the Source Code Form.

4. Inability to Comply Due to Statute or Regulation
---------------------------------------------------

If it is impossible for You to comply with any of the terms of this License
with respect to some or all of the Covered Software due to statute,
judicial order, or regulation, the inability to comply does not
terminate this License. You must:

(a) comply with the terms to the maximum extent possible; and

(b) describe the limitations and the affected Covered Software in a file
    accompanying the Covered Software.

